%% caption: Context falls into four classes: persistent, task, session, and tool. Each has a different freshness rule and update owner.
flowchart TB
    CTX[Context Engineering] --> R[Persistent Context<br/>AGENTS / architecture / glossary]
    CTX --> T[Task Context<br/>issue / brief / spec / ADR / AC]
    CTX --> S[Session Context<br/>Progress Note / open questions / next step]
    CTX --> L[Tool Context<br/>grep / verify / terminal log]
    R --> R1[stale-safe]
    T --> T1[issue-level canonical]
    S --> S1[mutable for restart]
    L --> L1[live and short-lived]
